As already stated, some of the answers which were given by the regarders were often not recorded upon the eyre rolls. Besides the six paragraphs relating to assarts, purprestures and wastes, the only answer which was usually recorded upon them was a list of persons having greyhounds within the forest. A few records, however, of the original regards presented to the justices in eyre have survived from which we may learn the manner in which all the Chapters were answered by the regarders.
